The murder case of farm manager Brendin Horner has been postponed to January. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The murder case of 21-year-old farm manager Brendin Horner has been postponed to January 2021. Horner was strangled and stabbed on a farm outside Paul Roux, Free State in October. READ: Brendin Horner murder accused return to court His murder led to much tensions, including violent protests in Senekal. The accused have denied any wrongdoing and told the court they intend to plead not guilty. Watch the video above for more details on this story.